WEBVTT

00:04.546 --> 00:06.423
{\an5}MAN:
<i>Sorry, kid.</i>
<i>Attempted suicide...</i>

00:06.506 --> 00:08.675
<i>attempted suicide...</i>
<i>attempted suicide...</i>

00:17.809 --> 00:19.728
♪ ♪

00:34.033 --> 00:36.786
(grunting)

00:36.870 --> 00:38.121
Daddy!

00:38.204 --> 00:40.457
(screaming)

00:40.540 --> 00:42.292
Val, what's the matter?
Are you okay?

00:42.375 --> 00:44.461
Hey, I heard a scream.
Are you all right?

00:44.544 --> 00:47.505
Yeah, yeah. It was just
a weird dream. I'm... I'm fine.

00:49.549 --> 00:51.259
You're sure you're okay?

00:51.342 --> 00:52.927
Yeah. You guys go back to bed.
I'm fine.

00:53.011 --> 00:54.512
It was just a dream.

00:58.391 --> 00:59.517
Good night.

01:05.648 --> 01:08.109
♪ ♪

01:34.677 --> 01:36.679
♪ ♪

02:00.537 --> 02:03.540
♪ ♪

02:34.279 --> 02:36.281
♪ ♪

02:42.871 --> 02:44.205
TONI:
Hello.

02:44.289 --> 02:46.124
School bus is here.

03:12.191 --> 03:13.776
You can take
the morning off, Bruno.

03:13.860 --> 03:15.278
{\an3}I'll, uh... I'll drive
the lady to school.

03:15.361 --> 03:16.779
I know. She told me.

03:16.863 --> 03:18.615
She'll be right down.

03:18.698 --> 03:19.949
{\an3}Doughnuts.

03:20.033 --> 03:21.117
My favorite.

03:21.200 --> 03:24.454
{\an1}Thanks.

03:24.537 --> 03:26.247
Hey, there you are.
Good morning.

03:26.331 --> 03:27.290
Good morning.

03:27.373 --> 03:28.625
So, are you ready to go?

03:28.708 --> 03:29.959
{\an1}I'm just finishing
my coffee.

03:30.043 --> 03:31.127
You want to come in?

03:31.210 --> 03:33.755
{\an3}I don't know. Is
your father in there?

03:33.838 --> 03:35.798
No. He's out of town.

03:35.882 --> 03:37.467
Come on. I'll give
you the grand tour.

03:37.550 --> 03:39.093
{\an3}All right.

03:49.771 --> 03:52.440
{\an1}This is quite
some humble abode.

03:52.523 --> 03:54.609
{\an3}My father built this place
about ten years ago.

03:54.692 --> 03:56.611
{\an3}After my mother
passed away,

03:56.694 --> 03:58.821
he really couldn't stay
in Dana Point anymore.

03:58.905 --> 04:00.865
{\an1}Yeah, I know
what that's like.

04:00.949 --> 04:02.742
My father died
two years ago.

04:02.825 --> 04:05.244
I'm sorry.

04:05.328 --> 04:07.580
{\an3}Come on.
Let's go in here.

04:11.793 --> 04:14.379
This is the
dining room.

04:14.462 --> 04:15.630
{\an3}Like it?

04:15.713 --> 04:17.714
Yeah. What's
not to like?

04:17.798 --> 04:18.882
Good. Because
you're going

04:18.966 --> 04:20.051
to be having dinner
here tomorrow night.

04:20.134 --> 04:21.719
{\an3}WYep.

04:21.803 --> 04:23.429
You and all
your closest friends.

04:23.513 --> 04:25.390
Excuse me?

04:25.473 --> 04:26.557
I knew, if I told you,

04:26.641 --> 04:27.642
you wouldn't let me
go ahead with it,

04:27.725 --> 04:28.977
so I got their numbers from Nat,

04:29.060 --> 04:31.604
{\an3}and I pretty much
invited everyone you know.

04:31.688 --> 04:33.564
Uh-huh. And you want
that kind of riffraff

04:33.648 --> 04:35.525
hanging out here
in your nice house?

04:35.608 --> 04:37.402
Yeah. I want
to get to know them,

04:37.485 --> 04:39.904
and I want them
to get to know me.

04:39.988 --> 04:41.906
Well, you were right
about one thing.

04:41.990 --> 04:43.700
If I <i> had</i> known, there's no way

04:43.783 --> 04:45.535
I would ever let
you go through with it.

04:49.664 --> 04:52.500
And this is my
father's study.

04:52.583 --> 04:55.169
This is actually my favorite
room in the house.

04:55.253 --> 04:58.589
{\an1}Everything in here has
special meaning to my father.

05:01.759 --> 05:03.678
See that desk?

05:03.761 --> 05:05.555
{\an5}When I was little,
I used to sit there
and do my homework.

05:05.638 --> 05:07.890
See, this is where
you and I differ,

05:07.974 --> 05:14.022
because me, I was never really
too big on the homework thing.

05:14.105 --> 05:15.440
Is this your dad?

05:15.523 --> 05:18.693
On the right. Yeah.

05:18.776 --> 05:20.695
Who's tI don't know.

05:20.778 --> 05:22.822
Must be a friend, or someone
he does business with.

05:26.951 --> 05:30.163
Thanks, Dad.

05:37.336 --> 05:39.589
{\an5}KELLY:
<i>I guess I'm going.</i>
<i>I mean, I said yes.</i>

05:39.672 --> 05:41.966
{\an1}I know. I mean, I was
so shocked when Toni called.

05:42.050 --> 05:44.135
{\an3}I know. Doesn't that
seem a bit pushy?

05:44.218 --> 05:45.762
{\an3}I mean, she hardly
even knows us.

05:45.845 --> 05:47.764
{\an1}Oh, come on. She's
just trying to be nice.

05:47.847 --> 05:49.432
{\an1}You're just jealous
because she likes Dylan.

05:49.515 --> 05:51.267
Am not!.

05:51.350 --> 05:54.687
Guys, regardless,
we still can't say no, right?

05:55.855 --> 05:57.106
Well, here you go.

05:57.190 --> 05:59.442
{\an1}A plate of fried food
for the tutor who got me

05:59.525 --> 06:01.110
{\an1}through my
first math quiz.

06:01.194 --> 06:03.279
Mmm! Onion rings
and french fries.

06:03.362 --> 06:05.114
HaOh, I seelf.

06:05.198 --> 06:06.449
{\an1}you've gotten him
up to fractions now.

06:06.532 --> 06:07.784
Have any of you

06:07.867 --> 06:09.077
{\an3}guys heard
or seen David

06:09.160 --> 06:10.119
in the last few days?

06:10.203 --> 06:11.287
{\an3}DONNA:
He hasn't been in class

06:11.370 --> 06:12.455
in the last week.

06:12.538 --> 06:13.623
I talked to Mel
the other day.

06:13.706 --> 06:16.584
{\an5}He said that he's
really depressed
about his mother.

06:16.667 --> 06:18.127
How's she doing?

06:18.211 --> 06:21.339
Not great. That's
why I'm worried.

06:38.022 --> 06:39.649
{\an1}Hey, Ma.

06:39.732 --> 06:41.192
How you doing?

06:41.275 --> 06:44.487
The doctor says
you're doing better.

06:46.114 --> 06:49.450
You look good.

06:49.534 --> 06:52.286
Nurse told me
you got a bath today.

06:58.960 --> 07:02.839
Would you talk to me, please?

07:02.922 --> 07:05.842
I know you're awake.

07:05.925 --> 07:09.053
Please?

07:10.638 --> 07:12.849
{\an1}Come on.
Let her rest.

07:21.899 --> 07:25.444
So when is she going
to get better?

07:25.528 --> 07:27.822
I've been through this
with her before, David.

07:27.905 --> 07:30.825
{\an1}You've got
to give it time.

07:30.908 --> 07:32.076
{\an3}Dad, she won't
even look at me.

07:32.160 --> 07:33.369
{\an3}She won't even
talk to me.

07:33.452 --> 07:35.997
{\an1}I know this has
been rough, David,

07:36.080 --> 07:37.832
but that's why we all
have to stay strong.

07:37.915 --> 07:41.836
Are you keeping up
with your classes?

07:41.919 --> 07:44.297
My classes? What,
are you kidding?

07:44.380 --> 07:46.716
{\an3}How can I concentrate
on school?

07:46.799 --> 07:49.010
{\an3}Do you just go to the
office and fill cavities

07:49.093 --> 07:50.428
{\an3}and pretend like
nothing is happening?

07:50.511 --> 07:53.598
{\an1}Actually, yes, I do.
Life goes on.

07:53.681 --> 07:55.892
Not for me.

07:55.975 --> 07:58.060
Could I talk to you
both for a moment?

07:58.144 --> 08:00.229
I wish I had
Hobetter news.g?

08:00.313 --> 08:03.524
{\an3}Come on.
Let's sit down.

08:05.985 --> 08:09.030
She's not responding
to the treatment?

08:09.113 --> 08:12.450
{\an3}We may have to get
more aggressive.

08:12.533 --> 08:13.701
What does that mean?

08:13.784 --> 08:14.869
When drug therapies

08:14.952 --> 08:17.914
don't work, we have to look
at alternative approaches.

08:17.997 --> 08:18.998
{\an1}Like what?

08:19.081 --> 08:21.083
Given her age, her physical
health and her history,

08:21.167 --> 08:23.920
my recommendation would
be a short course

08:24.003 --> 08:27.006
of low-level
electroconvulsive therapy.

08:28.174 --> 08:30.092
What? You mean
electric shock treatment?

08:30.176 --> 08:31.093
It may sound

08:31.177 --> 08:33.471
barbaric, but we know a lot more

08:33.554 --> 08:34.972
about ECT than we used to,

08:35.056 --> 08:37.099
and I have to tell you,
we've had some terrific results.

08:37.183 --> 08:38.433
{\an1}Isn't this
a little extreme?

08:38.517 --> 08:39.936
Actually, no.

08:40.019 --> 08:42.270
She's not coming out of this
depression. This may help.

08:42.355 --> 08:46.108
{\an3}Come on, Dad. You
can't let them do this.

08:46.192 --> 08:48.110
What exactly is involved?

08:48.194 --> 08:49.111
We sedate her,

08:49.195 --> 08:51.906
give her a heavy dose
of muscle relaxants.

08:51.989 --> 08:54.784
Then, through electrodes
attached to her skull,

08:54.867 --> 08:56.911
we administer
brief pulses

08:56.994 --> 08:59.163
{\an3}of low-voltage
electrical current.

08:59.247 --> 09:00.623
No more than that which

09:00.706 --> 09:04.043
would make a 100-watt bulb
flicker for just a second.

09:06.212 --> 09:07.964
And what are the side effects?

09:08.047 --> 09:10.466
{\an6}There may be
some short-term
memory loss.

09:10.549 --> 09:12.468
Studies show that
most missing memory

09:12.551 --> 09:14.303
returns within six months.

09:14.387 --> 09:18.599
{\an5}I also must tell you
there is a mortality
rate-- one in 20,000.

09:18.683 --> 09:20.309
You mean she could die?

09:20.393 --> 09:22.186
{\an3}For someone as depressed
as your mother,

09:22.270 --> 09:24.438
there's a lot greater chance
that,<i> without</i> this therapy,

09:24.522 --> 09:27.441
she'll attempt suicide again,
and succeed.

09:27.525 --> 09:31.028
No. No, forget
it, all right?

09:31.112 --> 09:32.863
You're not turning my mom
into a reading lamp.

09:32.947 --> 09:33.906
{\an1}David.

09:33.990 --> 09:35.491
I don't want to hear
anything else about this.

09:35.574 --> 09:36.826
All right, Dad?

09:51.382 --> 09:53.301
Why don't you get
a dorm room, man?

09:53.384 --> 09:54.885
You spend more time
on this campus than I do.

09:54.969 --> 09:56.387
{\an1}Yeah, well, I'm just
waiting for Toni.

09:56.470 --> 09:57.847
{\an1}She gets out of class
in a minute,

09:57.930 --> 09:59.181
{\an1}and we're going
to the beach.

09:59.265 --> 10:00.308
Ah! Young love.

10:00.391 --> 10:01.851
Ain't it grand?

10:01.934 --> 10:03.644
{\an3}So what's with
this dinner party?

10:03.728 --> 10:04.312
You coming?

10:04.395 --> 10:05.396
{\an3}Of course.

10:05.479 --> 10:06.814
{\an3}I can't wait to
meet the old man.

10:06.897 --> 10:08.399
Oh, neither can I.

10:08.482 --> 10:09.984
Too bad he's out of town.

10:10.067 --> 10:11.819
{\an1}She showed me around
the house the other day.

10:11.902 --> 10:14.030
You would not believe what
this guy has in his study.

10:14.113 --> 10:16.157
A signed confession?

10:16.240 --> 10:19.035
{\an1}A picture of him with his arm
around Jack. He's sick.

10:19.118 --> 10:20.328
And Toni doesn't know
anything about this?

10:20.411 --> 10:21.996
Not a clue.

10:22.079 --> 10:23.748
{\an3}Should be an
interesting evening.

10:23.831 --> 10:25.207
{\an1}Anybody else know
what you know?

10:25.291 --> 10:26.375
I haven't said a word.

10:26.459 --> 10:28.419
Yeah.it that way.

10:28.502 --> 10:30.379
Espresso, please.

10:30.463 --> 10:32.173
Actually, make
that a triple.

10:32.256 --> 10:34.175
Rough night, huh?

10:34.258 --> 10:36.927
Yeah. I didn't
get much sleep.

10:37.011 --> 10:38.179
{\an1}Anything you want
to talk about?

10:38.262 --> 10:39.555
No, I'll be all right.

10:39.639 --> 10:40.514
Do you want something?

10:40.598 --> 10:42.391
{\an1}No, thanks. I got a meeting
with my editor.

10:42.475 --> 10:44.143
{\an3}Oh, yes. The
illustrious Susan Keats.

10:44.226 --> 10:45.561
{\an3}You guys are
getting pretty cozy.

10:45.644 --> 10:47.229
Not as cozy
as I'd like.

10:47.313 --> 10:48.397
{\an3}Why don't you bring her
to the dinner party?

10:48.481 --> 10:50.232
{\an1}Already one step
ahead of you.

10:50.316 --> 10:51.525
Think she'll come?

10:51.609 --> 10:52.735
How could she say no?

10:52.818 --> 10:53.861
No.

10:53.944 --> 10:55.112
{\an3}Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Wait a minute.

10:55.196 --> 10:56.113
It's just a dinner party.

10:56.197 --> 10:57.031
What's the big deal?

10:57.114 --> 10:58.532
{\an3}A dinner party with
all your friends.

10:58.616 --> 10:59.575
So?

10:59.658 --> 11:01.243
{\an3}So I just
don't think

11:01.327 --> 11:03.412
{\an3}we should go out
together, that's all.

11:03.496 --> 11:06.582
Then what was that kiss about?

11:06.665 --> 11:09.043
{\an3}It was a moment
of weakness.

11:09.126 --> 11:11.170
Weak women--
my specialty.

11:11.253 --> 11:14.090
{\an3}You'll live to
regret that remark.

11:14.173 --> 11:16.133
Close the door.

11:20.346 --> 11:21.639
Sit down.

11:27.186 --> 11:29.105
You have a choice.

11:29.188 --> 11:30.439
I can fire you

11:30.523 --> 11:32.608
and we can go to the
dinner party, or...

11:32.692 --> 11:36.612
you keep your job
and we go our separate ways.

11:36.695 --> 11:38.280
That's ridiculous.

11:38.364 --> 11:39.615
I don't think so.

11:39.698 --> 11:41.450
I get it.

11:41.534 --> 11:43.953
You're afraid
of workplace romances.

11:44.036 --> 11:45.454
That's easy--
you fire me,

11:45.538 --> 11:47.790
we go to the dinner,
you rehire me tomorrow.

11:47.873 --> 11:48.582
Brandon, I'm serious, okay?

11:48.666 --> 11:50.251
Look, I know
we can get involved.

11:50.334 --> 11:52.128
I just don't happen
to think it's a good idea.

11:52.211 --> 11:54.630
So you <i> are</i> attracted to me.

11:54.713 --> 11:58.134
Oh, i-if I admit it,
will you go back to work?

11:58.217 --> 11:59.593
Sure.

11:59.677 --> 12:01.595
Okay, fine, I admit it.

12:01.679 --> 12:03.514
I am attracted to you.

12:03.597 --> 12:05.850
{\an6}I'm attracted to
a lot of things:
hot fudge sundaes,

12:05.933 --> 12:07.935
acid jazz, big headlines.

12:08.018 --> 12:11.021
Now, do me a favor,
go write your column.

12:21.907 --> 12:24.493
(laughs)

12:27.955 --> 12:29.665
(knocking)

12:29.748 --> 12:31.584
{\an1}DONNA:
David, open up, please.

12:31.667 --> 12:33.752
Go away, please.

12:34.837 --> 12:36.839
(knocking)

12:41.427 --> 12:43.345
(sighs)

12:46.807 --> 12:47.600
What?

12:47.683 --> 12:49.852
It's almost 2:00--
you're not up yet?

12:49.935 --> 12:51.020
No, I've been up.

12:51.103 --> 12:52.771
{\an6}KELLY:
You know, it
smells in here.

12:52.855 --> 12:55.316
{\an6}You should probably
open up some windows,
let some air in.

12:55.399 --> 12:56.984
Thanks.

12:57.067 --> 12:58.652
How's your mom doing?

12:58.736 --> 13:00.488
(wry chuckle):
She's nutty as a fruitcake.

13:00.571 --> 13:01.655
Haven't you heard?

13:01.739 --> 13:02.907
How about you?

13:02.990 --> 13:04.492
I'm fine.

13:04.575 --> 13:06.785
Would you guys
leave me alone now, please?

13:06.869 --> 13:08.037
David...

13:08.120 --> 13:09.997
{\an3}you have to get on
with your life.

13:10.080 --> 13:12.249
{\an1}And how long is that
supposed to take, Kel?

13:12.333 --> 13:14.210
Why don't you tell me
how I'm supposed to feel

13:14.293 --> 13:16.670
when the only hope for my mother
is if they attach electrodes

13:16.754 --> 13:17.880
to her head and fry her brain.

13:17.963 --> 13:19.673
I'm sorry.

13:19.757 --> 13:22.384
Be as sorry as you want to be.

13:24.929 --> 13:27.389
David, please
let us help, all right?

13:27.473 --> 13:28.891
You need some help.

13:28.974 --> 13:30.559
Thanks a lot, Kel.

13:30.643 --> 13:32.353
Maybe they should strap
electrodes to <i> my</i> head.

13:32.436 --> 13:33.896
Come on, you're
talking crazy.

13:33.979 --> 13:36.524
Maybe I am crazy.

13:36.607 --> 13:38.526
I don't know.

13:38.609 --> 13:40.486
Maybe it's in my blood.

13:41.570 --> 13:44.907
David, don't do this.

13:44.990 --> 13:47.618
{\an3}(exhales)

13:52.581 --> 13:54.083
(knocking)

13:54.166 --> 13:55.918
Who is it?

13:56.001 --> 13:57.253
It's Brandon.

13:57.336 --> 13:58.546
Brandon?!

13:58.629 --> 14:00.548
I'm really busy.

14:00.631 --> 14:02.967
{\an1}Well, this is
kind of important.

14:03.050 --> 14:05.094
Well, what do you want?

14:05.177 --> 14:08.222
You're not looking at me
through that peephole, are you?

14:08.305 --> 14:10.474
{\an1}(laughs):
Mm-hmm.o.

14:10.558 --> 14:11.976
Look, couldn't you
have used the phone?

14:12.059 --> 14:13.727
I'm right in the middle
of trying

14:13.811 --> 14:14.937
to finish with an article here.

14:15.020 --> 14:17.273
This will only
take a minute.

14:17.356 --> 14:18.857
(exhales)

14:21.151 --> 14:23.612
Okay, but only
for a minute.

14:23.696 --> 14:25.781
Can I, uh, come in?

14:25.864 --> 14:27.950
{\an3}Oh, yeah, sure,
come on in.

14:28.033 --> 14:30.953
Thanks.

14:31.036 --> 14:34.623
Wow. This is quite a place
you have here.

14:34.707 --> 14:35.958
Private bathroom and everything.

14:36.041 --> 14:38.294
You must know
all the right people.

14:38.377 --> 14:40.796
{\an3}Look, I really
am busy, so, um,

14:40.879 --> 14:41.964
what is it?

14:42.047 --> 14:43.632
All right, I'll get
right to the point.

14:43.716 --> 14:44.800
{\an1}I thought about it,
and I quit.

14:44.883 --> 14:47.094
You are not gonna
give up, are you?

14:47.177 --> 14:48.470
I think that
some things

14:48.554 --> 14:51.599
are more important than others,
and I think that...

14:51.682 --> 14:53.517
going out with you may be

14:53.601 --> 14:56.520
{\an1}more important than my job,
maybe, possibly, kinda,

14:56.604 --> 14:57.980
what do you think?

14:58.063 --> 14:59.982
{\an3}I'm not sure how
to take that.

15:00.065 --> 15:01.442
{\an1}Well, as an editor
you should be devastated,

15:01.525 --> 15:02.776
butAs a woman,...

15:02.860 --> 15:03.861
{\an3}I'm a little
concerned you have

15:03.944 --> 15:05.279
{\an3}this much trouble
getting a date.

15:05.362 --> 15:06.697
Is that a yes?

15:06.780 --> 15:08.991
{\an6}(sighs):
Well, a girl's
got to eat.

15:09.074 --> 15:11.869
{\an3}So, what time are you
gonna pick me up?

15:11.952 --> 15:13.162
Tomorrow night.

15:13.245 --> 15:15.706
I'll be here at 7:30,
right after I finish

15:15.789 --> 15:18.208
cleBrandon, relax.sk.

15:18.292 --> 15:19.710
You don't have to quit.

15:19.793 --> 15:21.045
You called my bluff.

15:21.128 --> 15:23.047
No, Didn't anyoneist.

15:23.130 --> 15:24.882
ever tell you that
when you strike oil

15:24.965 --> 15:26.216
that you stop drilling?

15:26.300 --> 15:29.011
No. So,(laughs) uh...

15:29.094 --> 15:30.971
I finished my column.

