you're paying me.

23:52.264 --> 23:54.224
{\an3}You don't have to keep
buttering me up.

23:54.307 --> 23:55.642
{\an1}It's okay.
You deserve it.

23:55.725 --> 23:58.478
Okay, if you insist.

23:58.562 --> 24:03.191
Mm. Now, Monday morning,
you've got another test.

24:03.275 --> 24:04.317
Are you prepared?

24:04.401 --> 24:05.944
You tell me.

24:09.781 --> 24:12.367
Very good.

24:12.450 --> 24:15.370
{\an1}Yeah, I'm actually getting
my money's worth out of you.

24:15.453 --> 24:17.914
{\an3}Yeah, you might even
pass the course.

24:17.998 --> 24:19.708
(chuckles)

24:19.791 --> 24:20.709
Don't do that.

24:20.792 --> 24:21.877
Do what?

24:21.960 --> 24:25.839
Don't take your arm away.
It felt good.

24:31.761 --> 24:33.555
{\an1}You have a date
for the dinner party tonight?

24:33.638 --> 24:37.392
Actually, I was, um,

24:37.475 --> 24:39.769
{\an3}I was gonna invite this guy
named, uh, Tenderheart.

24:39.853 --> 24:42.230
He's busy.

24:42.314 --> 24:46.610
{\an1}He's taking a girl
named Cuddles.

24:50.197 --> 24:51.114
{\an3}Steve?

24:51.198 --> 24:52.240
Yes?

24:52.324 --> 24:54.034
Are you playing
footsie with me?

24:54.117 --> 24:55.202
No.

24:57.662 --> 24:59.664
(shrieks): A mouse!

24:59.748 --> 25:00.916
GIRL:
What? Where?

25:00.999 --> 25:02.209
{\an3}A mouse!

25:04.044 --> 25:06.922
{\an3}Come on. We can talk
about this over dinner.

25:07.005 --> 25:08.924
I'm not hungry.

25:09.007 --> 25:14.262
{\an3}All right, then we'll
talk about it here.

25:14.346 --> 25:17.057
{\an3}I saw your mom's doctor
again this afternoon.

25:17.140 --> 25:21.061
{\an1}I'm not going along with
this electric shock stuff.

25:21.144 --> 25:22.437
You heard the
doctor, David.

25:22.520 --> 25:24.731
This could be
her only hope.

25:24.814 --> 25:26.733
{\an3}You have to
help me here.

25:26.816 --> 25:28.401
You have to talk to her.

25:28.485 --> 25:29.736
She won't listen to me.

25:29.819 --> 25:30.820
What's the difference?

25:30.904 --> 25:33.865
Why don't you just hook her up
and pull the switch?

25:33.949 --> 25:35.325
She has to give her permission.

25:35.408 --> 25:36.534
She has to sign a release.

25:36.618 --> 25:39.621
If she doesn't want to do it,
why should I convince her?

25:39.704 --> 25:42.249
Because your mom doesn't know
what's best for her now.

25:42.332 --> 25:43.416
We do.

25:45.585 --> 25:46.795
She won't even look at me.

25:46.878 --> 25:51.091
This isn't about <i> you,</i> David.

25:51.174 --> 25:53.134
This is about her.

25:53.218 --> 25:55.470
{\an1}You have to make
the effort for her.

25:55.553 --> 25:59.224
{\an1}Are you gonna back me up
on this?

26:20.412 --> 26:22.455
{\an3}Think we're fashionably
late enough?

26:22.539 --> 26:24.165
{\an1}I think we timed it
perfectly.

26:24.249 --> 26:26.334
{\an1}Are you sure I wore
the right dress?

26:26.418 --> 26:27.460
{\an3}Hi, guys.

26:27.544 --> 26:29.087
Uh, you wanna come on in?

26:29.170 --> 26:30.338
Kelly, you look stunning.

26:30.422 --> 26:32.090
Oh, thank you.
So do you.

26:32.173 --> 26:34.009
{\an4}(quietly):
I told you to go
with the red.

26:34.092 --> 26:35.093
Hmm.

26:35.176 --> 26:37.178
{\an3}This place makes us look
like <i> we're</i> from

26:37.262 --> 26:38.972
the wrong side
of the tracks.

26:39.055 --> 26:41.433
Well, at least you know she's
not after your money, Dylan.

26:41.516 --> 26:43.643
{\an4}Well, it must be
my dazzling sense
of humor.

26:43.727 --> 26:44.728
Oh, yeah.

26:44.811 --> 26:46.730
You're a regular
laugh riot, my friend.

26:46.813 --> 26:48.606
Hmm. Come here.

26:48.690 --> 26:50.025
Excuse me.

26:50.108 --> 26:52.402
{\an1}Don't start
with me, Brandon.

26:52.485 --> 26:53.862
Not here and not now.

26:53.945 --> 26:55.572
{\an5}You know what
the worst part
about this is?

26:55.655 --> 26:56.573
I really like Toni.

26:56.656 --> 26:58.241
Yeah, you're not
the only one.

26:58.325 --> 26:59.534
{\an1}TONI:
Look who's here.

26:59.617 --> 27:01.411
KELLY:
Hello.

27:01.494 --> 27:02.746
{\an3}Whoa,

27:02.829 --> 27:04.122
lady in red.

27:07.876 --> 27:09.878
{\an3}I'm suddenly feeling
very underdressed.

27:09.961 --> 27:11.546
Ah, she's just showing off.

27:13.340 --> 27:16.051
{\an3}She's got a lot
to show off.

27:16.134 --> 27:18.094
{\an1}Do I detect a twinge
of jealousy?

27:18.178 --> 27:20.722
When you're
dating a guy

27:20.805 --> 27:22.849
{\an3}whose ex-girlfriend happens
to be a cover girl,

27:22.932 --> 27:24.851
{\an3}you tend to get a
little self-conscious.

27:24.934 --> 27:26.811
(doorbell rings)

27:29.105 --> 27:32.400
That's all I'm saying.

27:32.484 --> 27:35.528
{\an6}Kelly looks absolutely
stunning tonight,
doesn't she?

27:35.612 --> 27:37.739
I really hadn't noticed.

27:37.822 --> 27:39.699
I was too busy
looking at you.

27:39.783 --> 27:41.576
Good answer.

27:42.660 --> 27:44.371
Thanks. Hi, guys.

27:44.454 --> 27:45.246
{\an3}Hi, Don.

27:45.330 --> 27:46.498
{\an1}TONI:
Hi, Donna.

27:46.581 --> 27:47.540
{\an1}Hey. I'm sorry
I'm late.

27:47.624 --> 27:48.541
Oh, don't worry about it.

27:48.625 --> 27:49.542
Where's Ray?

27:49.626 --> 27:50.418
He was gonna
pick me up,

27:50.502 --> 27:52.045
{\an3}but there's some big
pileup on the 405.

27:52.128 --> 27:53.380
He should be here soon.

27:53.463 --> 27:55.215
Well, that's what you
get for dating someone

27:55.298 --> 27:57.550
from Reseda.

27:57.634 --> 27:59.135
You Westside snob.

27:59.219 --> 28:00.637
I'll tell you
what, Donna.

28:00.720 --> 28:02.764
{\an3}Why don't you grab an hors
d'oeuvre or something?

28:02.847 --> 28:03.765
I'll be right back.

28:03.848 --> 28:04.933
Deserting me so soon?

28:05.016 --> 28:06.643
Well, nature calls.

28:08.144 --> 28:09.437
{\an1}Where's David?
Isn't he coming?

28:09.521 --> 28:11.940
{\an3}He called.
He isn't feeling well.

28:12.023 --> 28:14.484
{\an5}Excuse me. I'm gonna
go check something
out in the kitchen.

28:14.567 --> 28:15.652
Okay.

28:17.987 --> 28:20.240
{\an6}I feel like we
should be doing
something for David.

28:20.323 --> 28:22.450
I agree, but what?

28:22.534 --> 28:24.702
I wish I knew.

28:27.163 --> 28:29.791
Is this an Antista?

28:29.874 --> 28:33.503
{\an4}The last one I saw
was in New York at
the Whitney.

28:33.586 --> 28:37.132
{\an6}I see it as
a celebration of
line and form.

28:37.215 --> 28:41.010
{\an3}The negative space creating
a visual magnetism

28:41.094 --> 28:45.515
{\an3}and tensegritous relationship
between the tangent points.

28:45.598 --> 28:47.308
In other words?

28:47.392 --> 28:49.644
It makes me horny.

29:04.200 --> 29:06.077
Can I help you?

29:08.580 --> 29:09.789
I'm sorry.

29:09.873 --> 29:12.500
I know I'm not supposed
to be up here.

29:12.584 --> 29:13.626
I just had to see something.

29:13.710 --> 29:15.003
What's that?

29:15.920 --> 29:17.797
(sighs)

29:21.759 --> 29:22.802
This is my father.

29:22.886 --> 29:25.221
I know.

29:25.305 --> 29:26.639
I know who you are.

29:26.723 --> 29:29.058
Does Marchette?

29:29.142 --> 29:30.810
{\an3}Of course.

29:30.894 --> 29:32.145
Does Toni?

29:34.063 --> 29:35.565
I met your father.

29:35.648 --> 29:36.900
You're a lot like him.

29:36.983 --> 29:39.194
I don't know exactly
how to take that.

29:39.277 --> 29:42.530
Obviously, not everybody
thought that much of my dad.

29:42.614 --> 29:44.157
He was always right by me.

29:45.658 --> 29:47.785
I think you should go back
to the dinner party.

29:51.998 --> 29:54.209
