29:54.292 --> 29:56.753
{\an3}Antonia's like
a daughter to me.

29:56.836 --> 29:59.506
Don't forget that.

30:09.140 --> 30:10.892
(knocking)

30:10.975 --> 30:15.021
David, if you're in there,
please open up.

30:15.104 --> 30:16.022
David!

30:16.105 --> 30:17.273
He's not in there.

30:17.357 --> 30:18.274
Hey.

30:18.358 --> 30:21.069
{\an3}What do you guys do,
draw straws or something?

30:21.152 --> 30:23.696
{\an1}Excuse me?

30:23.780 --> 30:24.864
{\an3}Never mind.

30:24.948 --> 30:27.116
Listen, I just wanted
to see how you were.

30:27.200 --> 30:28.785
{\an1}I haven't seen you around
for awhile.

30:28.868 --> 30:32.038
{\an3}Yeah, well, I kinda want
to eat this while it's hot,

30:32.121 --> 30:34.374
{\an6}and I'm not really
in the mood for
any company.

30:34.457 --> 30:35.458
David, wait.

30:40.797 --> 30:42.715
How's your mom doing?

30:42.799 --> 30:46.886
Never better.

30:46.970 --> 30:49.889
{\an1}You want something
to eat?

30:49.973 --> 30:52.934
Um, no, thanks.

30:53.017 --> 30:56.437
{\an1}Listen, I know what
you're going through.

30:56.521 --> 30:57.605
Yeah, sure.

30:57.689 --> 30:58.648
No, I really do.

30:58.731 --> 31:01.609
A couple of months
before I moved out to L.A.,

31:01.693 --> 31:04.445
my father committed suicide.

31:09.826 --> 31:11.452
(exhales sharply)

31:11.536 --> 31:12.829
I'm sorry.

31:14.664 --> 31:16.124
You're scared, huh?

31:17.709 --> 31:18.960
Yeah.

31:19.043 --> 31:20.628
Me, too.

31:22.338 --> 31:23.965
Listen, why don't you come
with me?

31:24.048 --> 31:25.341
I want to show you something.

31:25.425 --> 31:26.426
Look, I'm really not

31:26.509 --> 31:30.471
in the mood to go anywhere
or see anyone right now.

31:30.555 --> 31:32.640
Do this for me.

31:34.058 --> 31:35.602
{\an1}Come on.
Get your jacket.

31:35.685 --> 31:37.729
{\an1}I'll take you
for a ride.

31:37.812 --> 31:39.105
Come on.

32:00.918 --> 32:03.046
{\an1}(sighs):
So what now?

32:05.923 --> 32:07.675
{\an3}Did you know they have
a mouse problem

32:07.759 --> 32:09.636
at the Peach Pit?

32:09.719 --> 32:10.720
{\an1}What?

32:10.803 --> 32:12.972
Yeah, Nat's going crazy.

32:13.056 --> 32:14.682
They keep setting traps,

32:14.766 --> 32:17.060
but the mouse keeps
stealing the cheese.

32:17.143 --> 32:17.977
Isn't that a riot?

32:18.061 --> 32:19.312
That's hysterical.

32:19.395 --> 32:22.690
{\an3}I kinda feel sorry
for the mouse, though.

32:22.774 --> 32:25.693
{\an1}Look, Val, I really
don't care, okay?

32:25.777 --> 32:27.070
{\an1}I don't care
about the Peach Pit.

32:27.153 --> 32:28.237
I don't care about mice.

32:28.321 --> 32:30.239
I don't care about anything
right now.

32:30.323 --> 32:32.200
What are we doing here?

32:34.452 --> 32:35.495
You'll see.

32:44.796 --> 32:47.715
{\an3}I found this place the first
week I was here in L.A.

32:47.799 --> 32:51.886
Yeah, it's a great view.

32:51.969 --> 32:55.598
{\an3}The view's not what
I come here for.

33:04.607 --> 33:05.525
You coming?

33:05.608 --> 33:07.026
{\an3}Would you get
back over here?

33:07.110 --> 33:08.361
There's slides all the time.

33:08.444 --> 33:09.195
That's right.

33:09.278 --> 33:11.072
The bottom can fall out
from under you

33:11.155 --> 33:13.574
without any warning at all.

33:15.118 --> 33:16.994
Just like life.

33:28.965 --> 33:30.800
(car horn blaring)

33:33.511 --> 33:35.221
Scared?

33:37.306 --> 33:40.435
Yeah, I'm scared.

33:40.518 --> 33:43.229
If you want to end it...

33:43.312 --> 33:45.106
here's your chance.

33:45.189 --> 33:46.441
If you want to
jump, go ahead.

33:46.524 --> 33:48.860
I won't stop you.

33:56.659 --> 33:58.745
What's the matter?

33:58.828 --> 34:02.290
Scared to die...

34:02.373 --> 34:05.293
(sniffling):
...or scared to live?

34:05.376 --> 34:07.628
{\an3}You know when the
demons get too close,

34:07.712 --> 34:10.922
the ones that say that I'm going
to end up like my father,

34:11.007 --> 34:14.177
{\an3}I come here for
a gut check.

34:22.726 --> 34:25.313
I don't want to die.

34:32.862 --> 34:34.864
I know.

34:48.668 --> 34:52.047
Toni, this was a perfect
end to a perfect evening.

34:52.130 --> 34:53.216
{\an3}Thank you.

34:53.299 --> 34:54.717
{\an3}I just wish Ray
could've made it.

34:54.801 --> 34:55.927
Well, he tried.

34:56.010 --> 34:56.886
{\an3}Just got
too late.

34:56.969 --> 34:58.846
{\an1}It is late.
We should get going.

35:01.098 --> 35:03.851
Hey, Nat, could we get
a check over here, please.

35:03.935 --> 35:05.603
{\an1}Yeah, I'll split that
with you, chief,

35:05.686 --> 35:07.313
although I'm not even sure

35:07.396 --> 35:08.439
exactly why I showed up.

35:08.523 --> 35:10.900
{\an1}Believe me, it wasn't exactly
a cakewalk for me either.

35:10.983 --> 35:13.194
{\an3}Then why don't you
do something about it.

35:13.277 --> 35:14.654
Tell Toni the truth.

35:14.737 --> 35:16.906
{\an4}I'm going to.
I'm just waiting
for the right time.

35:16.989 --> 35:20.409
{\an3}Would that be before or after
she falls in love with you?

35:21.410 --> 35:22.328
(loud snap)

35:22.411 --> 35:25.164
Willie, check the trap.

35:25.248 --> 35:26.582
I think we got him.

35:28.793 --> 35:29.752
{\an3}No luck.

35:29.836 --> 35:30.711
You little rat.

35:30.795 --> 35:33.089
{\an1}I'm gonna smash him when
I get my hands on him.

35:33.172 --> 35:34.340
Nat, Nat, Nat.

35:34.423 --> 35:36.425
You're handliI am?is all wrong.

35:36.509 --> 35:37.760
Why, Donna?

35:37.844 --> 35:39.720
{\an1}You got a better
mousetrap?

35:39.804 --> 35:41.389
As a matter of fact I do.

35:41.472 --> 35:42.473
Perhaps you guys should
stand back.

35:42.557 --> 35:45.351
I think I saw him go over
here behind the jukebox.

35:45.434 --> 35:46.894
{\an1}NAT:
What are you gonna do?

35:46.978 --> 35:50.147
Oh, it's very, very scientific.

35:51.315 --> 35:52.567
Come here, mousie.

35:52.650 --> 35:54.026
(tapping)

35:54.110 --> 35:56.779
squeaking)

35:56.863 --> 35:59.574
Come here, yeah.

35:59.657 --> 36:01.701
Is this the little mouse

36:01.784 --> 36:02.994
{\an3}you guys were
scared of?

36:04.120 --> 36:05.913
Get him out of here!

36:05.997 --> 36:08.499
Bye-bye, Mr. Mouse.
Have a nice life.

36:10.668 --> 36:12.378
Good night, guys.

36:12.461 --> 36:13.421
Good night, Don.

36:13.504 --> 36:16.382
{\an1}You sure got a way with
the critters, I'll tell you.

36:16.465 --> 36:17.466
{\an1}NAT:
Good night, Donna.

36:17.550 --> 36:18.593
You're my hero.

36:18.676 --> 36:20.428
{\an3}Bye, guys.

36:20.511 --> 36:21.804
{\an3}BOTH:
Bye, Donna.

36:21.888 --> 36:26.100
{\an3}And you're
my hero, Nat.

36:26.183 --> 36:27.977
{\an1}Don't you get
any ideas, Willie.

36:28.060 --> 36:29.562
(laughing)

36:33.190 --> 36:34.775
STEVE:
<i>Well, there you go.</i>

36:34.859 --> 36:36.444
Door to door service.

36:36.527 --> 36:38.779
Thanks.

36:38.863 --> 36:41.616
I had a really
good time tonight.

36:41.699 --> 36:43.784
Who would have thought?

36:43.868 --> 36:45.953
{\an3}Well, lots of
women actually.

36:46.037 --> 36:48.956
{\an3}Not that I want to pat
myself on the back.

36:49.040 --> 36:51.584
{\an1}I'll do it for you,
Steve. You're a stud.

36:51.667 --> 36:53.961
You know, Clare, I'm not
just another dumb blonde.

36:54.045 --> 36:55.463
{\an1}I know.

36:55.546 --> 36:58.132
And just because you're not
that great in math,

36:58.215 --> 36:59.467
doesn't mean you're not smart.

36:59.550 --> 37:02.428
I'm not that great
at English, either.

37:02.511 --> 37:05.097
I can tutor you in any
subject you want, Steve.

37:05.181 --> 37:07.850
Except one.

37:15.816 --> 37:17.485
A-plus.

37:29.288 --> 37:30.665
So, what do I say to her?

37:30.748 --> 37:33.668
You know what
to say to her.

37:33.751 --> 37:35.503
I'm nervous, okay?

37:35.586 --> 37:37.171
Don't be.

37:37.254 --> 37:39.215
She's your mother.

37:39.298 --> 37:42.218
What if I can't get
through to her?

37:42.301 --> 37:46.138
{\an3}Just tell her what
we talked about.

37:46.222 --> 37:50.268
All the things I didn't get
the chance to tell my dad.

37:50.351 --> 37:54.313
What about the, uh,
shock treatment stuff?

37:54.397 --> 37:55.523
I don't know.

37:55.606 --> 37:58.234
{\an3}Let the doctors
worry about that.

37:58.317 --> 38:01.570
You just worry about her
heart, not her head.

38:03.614 --> 38:06.075
Uh, thanks a lot
for everything.

38:06.158 --> 38:08.494
I don't know what I would
have done tonight

38:08.577 --> 38:10.871
if you hadn't come to drag me
out of the house.

38:10.955 --> 38:12.665
{\an3}Well, you're a crazy
person, David.

38:14.083 --> 38:16.836
It takes one to know one.

38:20.089 --> 38:22.258
Now go on in there.

38:48.909 --> 38:49.910
Hey, Mom.

38:53.998 --> 38:55.750
(sighs)

38:55.833 --> 39:00.046
Look, I know you don't want
to talk to me right now

39:00.129 --> 39:01.422
and that's fine,

39:01.505 --> 39:03.591
because you don't have
to look at me

39:03.674 --> 39:05.176
for me to talk to you.

39:09.638 --> 39:12.850
I know you're going through
a lot right now

39:12.933 --> 39:15.770
and believe me, I know
it's not your fault,

39:15.853 --> 39:18.606
{\an1}but I got to tell
you something.

39:18.689 --> 39:20.941
I want you to live.

39:21.025 --> 39:24.236
{\an1}It's real
important to me.

39:24.320 --> 39:27.448
We've got a lot
to look forward to.

39:27.531 --> 39:29.116
I mean, think about it.

39:29.200 --> 39:32.119
Someday, I'll be married
and have kids,

39:32.203 --> 39:34.872
and you'll be a grandmother.

39:36.874 --> 39:41.420
You got to get better for us
to share those things together.

39:49.011 --> 39:54.475
{\an1}Dad told me what...
what they want to do to you.

39:54.558 --> 39:56.769
And I know it
sounds scary,

39:56.852 --> 39:58.521
{\an1}but the doctor thinks
there's a real good chance

39:58.604 --> 39:59.814
it could make you better.

39:59.897 --> 40:02.691
Mom, you've got to give
it a chance...

40:02.775 --> 40:04.777
please.

40:07.905 --> 40:08.864
Do it for me.

40:08.948 --> 40:10.491
Do it for us.

40:17.206 --> 40:19.291
Give me your hand.

40:33.055 --> 40:34.849
Will you be there
when I wake up?

40:34.932 --> 40:37.685
{\an3}I want your face to be
the first one that I see.

40:37.768 --> 40:39.019
Yeah, I'll be here.

40:39.103 --> 40:41.647
Good.

40:41.730 --> 40:45.025
Now you better go home
and get some sleep.

40:45.109 --> 40:47.069
You look as if you could use it.

40:50.072 --> 40:52.199
Good night, Mom.

40:56.203 --> 40:58.164
Good night, David.

41:07.923 --> 41:09.717
{\an5}COLIN:
<i>You looked like</i>
<i>a million bucks tonight.</i>

41:09.800 --> 41:12.219
Really? You think so?

41:12.303 --> 41:13.762
Come on.

41:13.846 --> 41:15.514
I swear I saw Dylan
and Brandon's eyes

41:15.598 --> 41:17.600
pop out of their heads.

41:17.683 --> 41:20.561
Well, as it turns out,

41:20.644 --> 41:24.231
{\an3}I'm much more interested
in what you think.

41:24.315 --> 41:28.235
Well, I think...

41:28.319 --> 41:30.237
I love you.

41:38.329 --> 41:41.081
Stay the night?

41:41.165 --> 41:43.375
I brought my toothbrush.

41:53.510 --> 41:55.429
CINDY:
<i>"Dear Valerie,</i>

41:55.512 --> 41:58.390
"Jim and I are so sorry to hear
that you're having to go through

41:58.474 --> 42:00.809
"all those horrible
memories again.

42:00.893 --> 42:02.811
"I pray that as
the years go by,

42:02.895 --> 42:05.231
"your recollections
of the past will soften.

42:05.314 --> 42:07.942
"I can assure you,
you're not just a survivor,

42:08.025 --> 42:09.401
"you're a fighter.

42:09.485 --> 42:11.153
"And as you grow older,

42:11.237 --> 42:13.280
"those things that tear
at your soul

42:13.364 --> 42:16.450
"will make you a stronger
and more loving person.

42:16.533 --> 42:18.827
Best to you and Brandon,
Love(door opening)."

42:20.246 --> 42:21.372
Hey, Val.

42:21.455 --> 42:22.414
Hey, how did it go?

42:22.498 --> 42:24.083
You missed a great party.

42:25.376 --> 42:28.254
I didn't mean the party--

42:28.337 --> 42:29.421
I meant Susan.

42:29.505 --> 42:30.923
(chuckles)

42:31.006 --> 42:32.424
Good.

42:32.508 --> 42:34.969
So, that's all the dirt
I'm gonna get, huh?

42:35.052 --> 42:37.429
What can I say, I'm a gentleman.

42:37.513 --> 42:38.639
{\an3}Well, your mom
raised you right.

42:38.722 --> 42:41.475
You know, she's
a very wise woman.

42:41.558 --> 42:43.602
She had her moments.

42:45.896 --> 42:47.815
Well, I'm tired.

42:47.898 --> 42:48.983
{\an1}Hey Val,

42:49.066 --> 42:50.484
you going to be okay?

42:50.567 --> 42:53.279
Yeah.

42:53.362 --> 42:55.281
I may actually
get some sleep tonight.

42:57.533 --> 42:58.867
Good night.

42:58.951 --> 43:00.411
Good night.

43:04.707 --> 43:07.668
(moaning)

43:14.758 --> 43:17.678
(indistinct whispers)

43:20.973 --> 43:23.517
(whispers grow louder)

43:35.779 --> 43:39.616
You don't have
to be afraid anymore.
